## @riverpod Annotation Pattern

Riverpod 3.x uses code generation with the `@riverpod` annotation. This is the **primary pattern** used in {{PROJECT_TITLE}}.

### Critical Rule: Initialize in build(), NOT Constructor

⚠️ **CRITICAL**: Never initialize state or read providers in the constructor. Always use the `build()` method.

```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Initialization in constructor
@riverpod
class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier extends _${{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier {
  {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier() {
    // This runs BEFORE providers are available!
    _load{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Plural();
  }

  @override
  Future<List<{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Entity>> build() => Future.value([]);

  Future<void> _load{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Plural() async {
    // This will fail because providers aren't ready
    final useCase = ref.read(get{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}PluralUseCaseProvider);
  }
}
```

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT - Initialization in build()
@riverpod
class {{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier extends _${{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}ListNotifier {
  @override
  Future<List<{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}Entity>> build() async {
    // Providers are available here
    final get{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}PluralUseCase = ref.read(get{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}PluralUseCaseProvider);
    return await get{{PRIMARY_ENTITY}}PluralUseCase.execute();
  }

  Future<void> refresh() async {
    // Invalidate to trigger rebuild
    ref.invalidateSelf();
  }
}
```

### Basic AsyncNotifier Pattern

```dart
import 'package:riverpod_annotation/riverpod_annotation.dart';

part 'my_provider.g.dart';

@riverpod
class MyNotifier extends _$MyNotifier {
  @override
  Future<DataType> build() async {
    // Initialize here - providers are available
    final useCase = ref.read(myUseCaseProvider);
    return await useCase.execute();
  }

  Future<void> performAction() async {
    // Set loading state
    state = const AsyncValue.loading();

    // Execute and handle result
    state = await AsyncValue.guard(() async {
      final result = await someAsyncOperation();
      return result;
    });
  }

  Future<void> refresh() async {
    // Invalidate to trigger rebuild
    ref.invalidateSelf();
  }
}
```

### Basic Notifier Pattern (Synchronous)

```dart
@riverpod
class MySyncNotifier extends _$MySyncNotifier {
  @override
  DataType build() {
    // Return initial state
    return DataType.initial();
  }

  void updateValue(DataType newValue) {
    // Update state
    state = newValue;
  }

  void reset() {
    // Reset to initial
    state = DataType.initial();
  }
}
```

